Class DefaultParametersValues

      • DEFAULT_REFERENCE_WINDOW_SIZE

        public static final int DEFAULT_REFERENCE_WINDOW_SIZE
        Past list reference buffer size. If this value gets bigger, more lists are kept on the buffer, increasing the chances of finding a better reference candidate and therefor increasing compression. But it will increase the usage of memory and the time required to find a reference candidate.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_MIN_REFERENCE_LIST_SIZE

        public static final int DEFAULT_MIN_REFERENCE_LIST_SIZE
        Minimum size of reference list. Smaller lists are discarded from the potential candidates set.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DEFAULT_MAX_RECURSIVE_REFERENCES

        public static final int DEFAULT_MAX_RECURSIVE_REFERENCES
        Maximum number of reference that a reference list can have in order to be use a reference. Increasing this numbers increases the chances of finding a better reference candidate and therefor increasing compression. But it will increase the time required to decompress a list.
        See Also:
